Regal Named Best Australian Hedge Fund for Long-Short Strategy

-- B y   J a c o b   G r e b e r
-- 
2011-09-15T11:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/regal-named-best-australian-hedge-fund-for-long-short-strategy.html
Regal Funds Management Pty Ltd.,
which oversees about A$1 billion ($1.03 billion) in assets, was
named  Australia ’s hedge fund of the year for its Tasman Market
Neutral Fund, which has gained 27.4 percent so far in 2011.  The Sydney-based fund generated positive returns in seven
of the first eight months of this year, while the nation’s
benchmark S&P/ASX 200 index has declined for five straight
months. The title was awarded at a function in Sydney today by
the local arm of industry group the  Alternative Investment
Management Association .  Evergreen  Capital Partners , based in  Melbourne , won best
emerging manager. The best long short & absolute return fund was
awarded to Optimal Australia Absolute Trust, according to an e-
mailed statement from the association.  A panel of judges including Damien Hatfield, an industry
consultant at Triple A Partners in Sydney, 358Australia Pty Ltd.
Chairman Simon Ibbetson, and  Perpetual Ltd. (PPT) ’s Oliver Mauger,
ranked more than 150 funds on criteria that included their
absolute returns and outperformance against peers, the
association said.  Regal beat the Melbourne-based Bennelong Long Short Equity
fund and Macquarie’s Asian Alpha Fund for the top award,
according to the association.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jacob Greber in Sydney at 
